description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for an experienced Supervisor to join our Housekeeping Team at Brighton &amp; Sussex University Hospitals NHS Trust. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, innovative and qualified professional to lead the housekeeping and patient feeding services across the site with particular focus on improving the patient experience. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is a Band 3 position for 37.5 hours weekly to be worked over 5 days (Monday – Sunday with flexibility to cover shifts rotationally as required).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is a high profile role and requires a competent and experienced supervisor who will be responsible for the delivery of high standards of cleaning and support to a large team of Housekeeping Assistants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The aim of this post is to ensure a clean and safe environment for patients and staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates should have excellent people management skills and have the ability to develop and embed a performance driven team culture. The successful candidate will need to demonstrate highly effective communication and be able to lead a customer focused team. You will be keen to explore new ideas whilst striving to ensure the Trust continues to deliver an effective and high quality cleaning &amp; patient catering service.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you have a proven track record of being able to deliver a high quality services this could be the role for you and we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Antoinette Thomas&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Housekeeping Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address Antoinette.Thomas1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
